    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-26T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-26T06:00:00-05:00" n="797"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d797">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.00/790: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-26T20:00:00+09:00"
                            >May 26, 1938—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 26—7:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>332. It has just been announced that following Cabinet appointments were made
                    this afternoon: Foreign Affairs, General Ugaki; Finance and Commerce and
                    Industry, Seishin Ikeda; Education, General Araki. Comment follows.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
